title: H.S. football: Rutherford’s Kevin Kosakowski scores seven touchdowns in win over Palisades Park/Leonia - Sports
text:
Buy this photo FILE PHOTO BY JIM CLARKE/SPECIAL TO THE RECORD Rutherford Kevin Kosakowski (7) scored seven touchdowns, six on the ground and one on a catch, in the Bulldogs’ win over Palisades Park/Leonia. Kevin Kosakowski rushed for six touchdowns and caught a TD pass to power Rutherford over Palisades Park/Leonia, 50-20, in an NJIC football game Friday night at Rutherford.
Kosakowski scored on runs of 32, 30, 26, 10, 46 and 4 yards, and hauled in a 61-yard scoring strike from Nick Birchby as the Bulldogs (4-0) led, 50-12, after three quarters.
Marcus Marson had touchdown runs of 6 and 57 yards for the Tigers (1-3).
WEEHAWKEN 14, BOGOTA 6 (at Bogota) — Joan Andujar carried 29 times for 166 yards and two touchdowns to lift the Indians (3-1) to their third straight win. D’Anthony Flores led Weehawken with 10 tackles, and Keith Hablitz had eight tackles and a sack.
Brennen Rodgers rushed for a 10-yard TD for the Buccaneers (1-3).
LYNDHURST 41, HARRISON 19 (at Harrison) — Peter Guerriero carried 15 times for 230 yards and four touchdowns to pace the Golden Bears (1-3).
Michael O’Donnell had TD runs of 2, 70 and 8 for the Blue Tide (0-4).
CRESSKILL 32, SECAUCUS 6 (at Secaucus) — Nick Carroll rushed for three 5-yard touchdowns and three two-point conversions to lead the Cougars (3-1).
Evander Pons had a 15-yard TD run for the Patriots (0-4).
GARFIELD 27, MANCHESTER 0 (at Garfield) — Aveon Irving ran for 141 yards and two touchdowns on eight carries, and returned the second-half kickoff 80 yards for a score to power the Boilermakers (4-0) over the Falcons (2-2). Matt Wierzba and Matt Delorenzo each recovered a fumble for Garfield.
WOOD-RIDGE 32, EMERSON 0 (at Emerson) — Josh Paez had 250 yards and two touchdowns on 25 rushes, and added 12 tackles on defense to lead the Blue Devils (1-3) over the Cavos (0-4). Mike Giancaspro ran for 50 yards and two TDs on six carries, and had eight tackles.
HASBROUCK HEIGHTS 55, NORTH ARLINGTON 0 (at North Arlington) — Evan Georgatos and Seth Scalvino each had two rushing touchdowns to power the Aviators (3-1) over the Vikings (2-2).
BIG NORTH 
TENAFLY 6, DEMAREST 0 (at Tenafly) — Max Miller ran for a 30-yard touchdown, one play after Ethan Feingold recovered a fumble as the Tigers (1-3) defeated the Norsemen (0-4). Thomas Rafferty had seven tackles and an interception for Tenafly.
RIVER DELL 34, FORT LEE 12 (at Fort Lee) — Dylan Connolly rushed for touchdowns of 44 and 2 yards, and Alec Lanza returned a blocked punt 32 yards for a score and added a 60-yard TD run to lift the Golden Hawks (5-0) over the Bridgemen (0-4).
WAYNE VALLEY 28, WEST MILFORD 0 (at West Milford) — Nick Goodwin had touchdown runs of 29, 2 and 9 yards, and threw a 22-yard TD pass to Vincent Tedesco to lead the Indians (4-0) over the Highlanders (1-3).
MAHWAH 35, DUMONT 0 (at Dumont) — James Ciliento had touchdown runs of 15, 17 and 6 yards, and threw an 18-yard TD pass to Zayjay Colon-Carrero to send the Thunderbirds (4-0) past the Huskies (1-3).
NORTHERN HIGHLANDS 54, PASSAIC 7 (at Allendale) — Liam Wilczynski carried 21 times for 263 yards and two touchdowns, and caught four passes for 60 yards and a score to power the Highlanders (2-2). Noah Abdalla went 9-of-13 for 149 yards and three TDs, and ran for a 1-yard score.
Quamir Williams had a 70-yard kickoff return touchdown for the Indians (0-3).
RAMAPO 53, PASSAIC VALLEY 0 (at Franklin Lakes) — Joe O’Hagan had touchdown runs of 16, 15 and 5 yards as the Green Raiders (3-1) jumped out to a 40-0 halftime lead over the Hornets (0-4). Ryan Curtiss ran for a 10-yard TD and caught a 70-yard scoring pass from Tom Jaten, who threw for two touchdowns.
NJAC 
PEQUANNOCK 33, WHIPPANY PARK 14 (at Pequannock) — Justin Brunda and Sean Klimek each rushed for two touchdowns to lift the Golden Panthers (3-1).
